            <bug_when>2009-04-15 16:57:12 +0200</bug_when>
            <thetext>Changing the icons in the Test Runner&#39;s tree view to reflect the tests&#39; results causes massive slowdown in Internet Explorer 6/7/8. Test packages take somewhere between five and ten times longer to run. This effect is present but barely noticeable in other browsers. It seems that recursively walking up the tree each time a test finishes is extremely expensive in IE.</thetext>
          </long_desc>
